SIMPLE: excitant
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Excitant
<hw>Ex*cit"ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>excitans</ets>, <ets>-antis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>excitare</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>excitant</ets>.]</ety> <def>Tending to excite;
exciting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excitant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Excitant
<hw>Ex*cit"ant</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>An agent
or influence which arouses vital activity, or produces increased action,
in a living organism or in any of its tissues or parts; a
stimulant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excitate</ent>⟦br⟧
